item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: doem55
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: About
item.dc:creator: doem55
item.content:encoded: My name is Emmet McDonnell, I am 30 years of age and I am from Castleknock. I will be entering my 3rd year of College in September as part of a 4 year course. I am studying Creative Digital Media in The Institute of Technology Blanchardstown. Its a course which I love very much and have learned many skills including photography, graphic design, animation, web design, sound engineering, video production and editing amongst others. I have a passion for digital media in my everyday life which I want to continue carrying out in my professional life.

item.title: Video
item.dc:creator: doem55
item.content:encoded: [embed]https://vimeo.com/193362291[/embed] Short Film Project This is a short film rough cut that myself and 2 other students are in the process of making for a Drama Filmmaking module. I came up with the concept and wrote the script. I am also the director, cameraman and one of the main actors in it. The concept of the film itself is based upon a patient suffering from paranoid schizophrenia and his doctor in a psychiatric ward. Over the course of a number of incidents, the patient and doctor transcend mental states. The final cut is due next week. [embed]https://vimeo.com/190854206[/embed] Audio Re-dub This is an audio re-dub that I did for my Sound Design module. None of the filming was carried out by myself but I recreated the sound effects, dialogue, foley and ambience entirely from scratch. This required recording all of these sounds on a zoom mic as well as editing and transforming them using applications such as Reaper and Audacity. I then composed and structured the sound with the video file in Premiere Pro so that it kept in time with the movie. [embed]https://vimeo.com/186193067[/embed] Audio Re-Dub This is another audio re-dub that I did. This time I used a scene from one of my favourite movies in Drive. For this I had to source a lot of the sounds from online sound banks as well as create some of them myself. While doing this project I realised what a tough job a sound editor carries out but when I finished it I felt a great sense of satisfaction when I witnessed it match up so well. [embed]https://vimeo.com/165484128[/embed] The Captain of Silverpine Studios This was part of my Documentary Filmmaking module. We based it upon the founder of Ireland's first film studio which included sourcing a lot of the stock footage from the archives in Bray. The film company has since finished due to the introduction of colour tv but for some time it was leading the way for Irish television. It accounts for the beginning of the company and we filmed and recorded sound for a number of interviews which included people who used to work at the studios. We gathered all of the workers who were meeting up for a reunion. [embed]https://vimeo.com/151141372[/embed] Music Video (Moderat - A New Error) This was a music video which I shot with my own camera. It included gathering a number of scenes of original footage as well as blending them with stock footage. I chose a song from one of my favourite artists and tried to edit in the way which took into account the progression of the song as well as the timing of the beat. [embed]https://vimeo.com/109017857[/embed] Educational Slide Show This was a project where we had to demonstrate different video effect including transitions in audio as well as images. I based mine upon the Hubble Telescope as I have always enjoyed researching the topic of space exploration. I used this for a number of projects as its something that I am passionate about.
